    "Figure 2 shows the observing timeline for all the spectra in the selected MRS timedomain sample of solar-like stars.",
    "The dates of the spectra span five observing years of MRS (from September 2017 to June 2022).",
    "The absence of observations in July and August of each calendar year (time slots indicated by the vertical dotted lines in Figure 3 shows the distribution histogram of N obs (number of MRS observations of each stellar source; see definition in Section 3.2.1) for all the stellar sources in the selected MRS time-domain sample of solar-like stars.",
    "It can be seen from Figure 3 that the value of N obs in our sample varies in the range from 3 to 31, and the number of stellar sources corresponding to each N obs value has the trend of rapid decrease with the increase of N obs.",
    "Figure 4 shows the distribution histogram of T span (time span of multiple observations of each stellar source; see definition in Section 3.2.1) for all the stellar sources in the selected MRS time-domain sample of solar-like stars."
